radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid filled appendix measuring up to 1.5cm with mural enhancement and significant surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of extraluminal air or local fluid collection to suggest perforation. Lung bases are clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver enhances homogeneously, gallbladder is distended without wall edema, kidneys are normal, and the GI tract shows no evidence of obstruction.
